They are the fundamental basis of the paradigms and methodologies that will be applied throughout our system.

### Accessibility

Our products should be usable for any user. We must build products that are perceivable and operable.

### Consistency

All teams must have the same objective and must speak to the user in the same way, whether visually or in writing.

### Reusable

Every hour we invest in a component should serve to build and prevent you or someone else from having to rebuild our work.

### Shareable

We must build and work with tools that allow us to share all our work.

### User Control

The user must have a sense of control over the product.

### Forgiveness

We must allow the user to change their mind or repeat a process.

### Perception of Stability

Even with robust and complex platforms, the user must perceive processes as simple and familiar as possible.
